00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:57.000
And it's pure Phrygian 

00:23:57.000 --> 00:23:59.000
But the real 

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:02.000
surprise is to find that even old 

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.000
German Brahms has used 

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.000
this mode — very unusual for him -- in 

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:11.000
the slow movement of his 4th Symphony.

00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:14.000
I'm sure you've all heard this solemn 

00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:35.000
and majestic phrase:

