00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:41.000
All right, up we 

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:43.000
climb to the next mode, 

00:24:43.000 --> 00:24:46.000
called the Lydian. This one, as you 

00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:50.000
might guess, begins on F, and like the 

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:52.000
others, uses only white notes all the 

00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:54.000
way up the octave 

00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:57.000
That's the Lydian mode. Now what makes 

00:24:57.000 --> 00:24:58.000
this one different from the other two 

00:24:58.000 --> 00:25:00.000
modes we've already talked about? Two 

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:03.000
things: first, that it is a major mode 

00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:05.000
the first one we've 

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:09.000
